      "writtenOn": "2019-02-13T05:59:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We now also need \"Update\", for cases when service accounts for existing projects in projects.cfg change (this is allowed).\n\nI think \"Create\" can be changed to be an upsert operation (https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/upsert) taking *ProjectIdentity as input:\n\nUpdate(c context.Context, identity *ProjectIdentity) error {\n  1. Lookup the existing one if any.\n  2. Do nothing if already matches \u0027identity\u0027.\n  3. Otherwise ds.Put(...) new identity (which will either create the entity or update existing one).\n}\n\n(this will also make the operation idempotent, which is nice)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 43,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 43,
        "endChar": 27
      },
      "revId": "9457de6f70215b5b2cdc0d094f6f99d121daca34",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
